long executeLargeUpdate(String) Executes the given SQL statement, which may be an INSERT, UPDATE, or DELETE statement or an SQL statement that returns nothing, such as an SQL DDL statement.

long getLargeMaxRows() Retrieves the maximum number of rows that a ResultSet object produced by this Statement object can contain.
long getLargeUpdateCount() Retrieves the current result as an update count; if the result is a ResultSet object or there are no more results, -1 is returned.
void setLargeMaxRows(long) Sets the limit for the maximum number of rows that any ResultSet object generated by this Statement object can contain to the given number.
